      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:1:32:3",
      "text": [
        " الْغُلَامُ لَا يُلْقِحُ حَتَّى يَتَفَلَّكَ ثَدْيَاهُ وَ تَسْطَعَ رِيحُ إِبْطَيْهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, from Abu Abdullah, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from his<sup>asws</sup> father<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The boy cannot impregnate until his breasts are rounded, and the smell of his armpits rises’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Nawfaliy from al-Sakuniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has narrated from his father, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, who has said, that a boy cannot impregnate until his breast becomes round and the smell of his armpit rises strong.’” "
        ]
      }
